The All Progressives Congress, APC, has extended registration of members and revalidation till the end of March. The exercise was initially scheduled to end on February 23. APC Director of Organisation, Prof. Al-Mustapha Ussiju Medaner, made this known in a statement on Sunday. He said the registration will now end on 31 March, due to demands across the states for an extension in order to accommodate all prospective members, Part of the statement read: “We have gotten a nationwide acknowledgement of the increasing popularity of the All Progressive Congress, APC and most especially in states and regions that are being governed by the opposition party. “We will shift the end of the registration exercise to Wednesday 31st March, 2021. “All Committee members have been advised to remain in their places of assignment as additional disbursement of registration materials to meet up with the demands reported in most states.”